about.description:
Conda lock is a lightweight library that can be used to generate fully
reproducible lock files for conda environments.
It does this by performing multiple solves for conda targeting a set of
platforms you desire lockfiles for.
This also has the added benefit of acting as an external presolve for conda
as the lockfiles it generates results in the conda solver not being invoked
when installing the packages from the generated lockfile.

name: conda-lock
raw_recipe:
{% set version = "2.1.2" %}

package:
  name: conda-lock
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/c/conda-lock/conda_lock-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 4a51f04a962ec563e8b8d133fa214012ad0f284967abb49877d5b5340283165c

build:
  number: 0
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv
  noarch: python
  entry_points:
    - conda-lock = conda_lock:main

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.8
    - hatchling
    - hatch-vcs
    - pip
  run:
    - python >=3.8
    - click >=8.0
    - click-default-group
    - ensureconda >=1.3
    - gitpython >=3.1.30
    - jinja2
    - pydantic >=1.10
    - pyyaml >=5.1
    - tomli
    - typing_extensions
    - ruamel.yaml
    - toolz >=0.12.0,<1.0.0
    - cachecontrol-with-filecache >=0.12.9
    - cachy >=0.3.0
    - clikit >=0.6.2
    - crashtest >=0.3.0
    - html5lib >=1.0
    - keyring >=21.2.0
    - packaging >=20.4
    - pkginfo >=1.4
    - requests >=2.18
    - tomlkit >=0.7.0
    - virtualenv >=20.0.26
    - urllib3 >=1.26.5,<2.0

test:
  imports:
    - conda_lock
  commands:
    - pip check
    - conda-lock --help
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://github.com/conda/conda-lock
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Lightweight lockfile for conda environments
  description: |
    Conda lock is a lightweight library that can be used to generate fully
    reproducible lock files for conda environments.
    It does this by performing multiple solves for conda targeting a set of
    platforms you desire lockfiles for.
    This also has the added benefit of acting as an external presolve for conda
    as the lockfiles it generates results in the conda solver not being invoked
    when installing the packages from the generated lockfile.
  doc_url: https://conda.github.io/conda-lock/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - maresb
    - mariusvniekerk
    - ocefpaf
    - bollwyvl
